---

## ğŸ§¹ Data Cleaning & Preparation

- Converted columns to appropriate data types
- Renamed columns for clarity
- Handled null values by replacing them with zeros
- Removed duplicate records
- Sorted data by date
- Created additional columns (Year, Month) for time-based analysis
- Validated data consistency for confirm
## ğŸ“ DAX Measures Created
- Total Confirmed Cases  
- Total Deaths  
- Total Recovered  
- Active Cases  
- Death Rate (%)  

These measures enabled accurate KPI calculations and dynamic visuals.

---

## ğŸ“Š Dashboard Features
The Power BI dashboard includes:
- KPI cards showing total confirmed, deaths, recovered, and active cases
- Line chart for COVID-19 trends over time
- Bar chart displaying top affected countries
- Map visualization for country-wise case distribution
- Interactive slicers for country and date selection

---

## ğŸ” Key Insights
- Significant spikes in confirmed cases during early pandemic phases
- Variation in death rates across countries
- Recovery trends improved over time in several regions
- Certain countries consistently reported higher active cases

